# Project

ERCS-20 / Orbix — 代币化股权 + 内置 AMM 的 Web3 前端（Phase 1：Swap、Factory；Phase 2：spot/futures/pools 占位）。

Tech stack: Next.js 16 App Router, React 19, TypeScript, Tailwind CSS v4, shadcn/ui, wagmi, viem, RainbowKit, TanStack Query, next-themes, sonner.

## Directory

| Path | Role |
|------|------|
| `app/` | Routes, `layout.tsx`, `globals.css` — keep pages thin |
| `components/ui/` | shadcn primitives (CLI only) |
| `components/<feature>/` | Feature UI |
| `hooks/` | Client hooks |
| `lib/web3/`, `lib/wagmi/`, `lib/contracts/`, `lib/config/` | Chain & contracts |
| `lib/i18n/messages/` | en / zh-CN / zh-TW |
| `providers/` | AppProviders, Web3, theme, i18n |

See `.cursor/README.md` for rules/skills index.

## Always

- Use App Router; prefer Server Components; Client only when needed (wallet, theme, i18n, forms).
- Write strict TypeScript; prefer composition over inheritance.
- Use `bigint` for on-chain amounts; `parseUnits` / `formatUnits` (viem) for decimals.
- Use formatted strings for display only; UTC for timestamps; order/tx IDs as strings.
- Wait for transaction receipt before treating writes as successful.
- Minimal diff — only touch task-related files.
- When adding npm packages: list names in reply + give `npm install …`; user runs install locally (do not assume install succeeded in agent env).

## Never

- Use `any` or ignore TypeScript errors.
- Add libraries without clear need (see `security.mdc`).
- Duplicate components or put business logic inside presentational UI.
- Mix unrelated UI refactors with Web3 changes in one diff.
- Use `number` for token amounts or float for price math internally.
- Commit `.env.local` or secrets; create git commits unless user asks.
